body.prompt: Respond to this question and explain your answer. Complete the sentence using one word: Roses are red, violets are

choices.text:
blue.

I completed the sentence with "blue" because it is a common completion used to complete the traditional nursery rhyme, which ends with:

Roses are red,
Violets are blue.

The complete rhyme is often remembered and recited as follows:

Roses are red,
Violets are blue,
Sugar is sweet,
And so are you!
